            <app loc="2"><note>tThe stone has ΕΥϹ; Cormack reported an upright after this, but A seems clear. Otherwise εὐϲ<unclear>ε</unclear><supplied reason="lost">βωϲ</supplied>
                would be an attractive restoration</note></app>
            <app loc="3"><rdg resp="#mama8">ἁγίασμ<supplied reason="lost">α</supplied></rdg> <note>but there is room for 3-4 letters thereafter, and something more seems necessary to make sense of TO in line 4</note></app>
           </listApp>
